So if plate shouldn't mitigate better than leather, then I guess we don't need different types of armors huh? I mean, why have them when they have the same mitigation?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
But you see we dont have different types of armours in EQ... I wish people would grasp that.<br>
<br>
A piece of armour with 20ac is a piece of armour with 20ac *fullstop*... whether or not it can be worn by a paticular toon is down to how it is flagged for Race, Class, Deity and Level.... that's it.<br>
<br>
In a future game it may or may not be desirable for different armour types to have differing properties based upon said type, but this is not that game. It's not supported, and the overhaul to suport armour types would be huge. We can wait until SWG or EQ2 to see if VI roles armour types into a game.<br>
<br>
Calling a class an int caster a cloth class merely reflects a guiding principle for itemisation, not a game mechanic. And the suit of enchanted elven chain the int caster is decked out in is only notionally chain armour, there's nothing in the game mechanics to actually flag it thus, and it differs only from other armour items in it published stats, not in the utility of those stats.<br>
<br>
An fungi tunic looks like chain on humans and plate on Iksar... it's neither its just a fungi tunic, any notion of what type of armour it might be is merely that, a notion. Not an actuality. <p><hr />
